            <fr:title text="Closure of bijections under identity and composition">Closure of <fr:link href="jms-00KR.xml" title="Bijection" addr="jms-00KR" type="local">bijections</fr:link> under <fr:link href="jms-00II.xml" title="The identity relation" addr="jms-00II" type="local">identity</fr:link> and <fr:link href="jms-00IN.xml" title="Relational composite" addr="jms-00IN" type="local">composition</fr:link></fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Theorem</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><fr:p>The <fr:link href="jms-00KI.xml" title="Closure of functions under identity and composition" addr="jms-00KI" type="local">identity function</fr:link> is a <fr:link href="jms-00KR.xml" title="Bijection" addr="jms-00KR" type="local">bijection</fr:link>, and the <fr:link href="jms-00IN.xml" title="Relational composite" addr="jms-00IN" type="local">composition</fr:link> of <fr:link href="jms-00KR.xml" title="Bijection" addr="jms-00KR" type="local">bijections</fr:link> yields a <fr:link href="jms-00KR.xml" title="Bijection" addr="jms-00KR" type="local">bijection</fr:link>.</fr:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>23</fr:day></fr:date><fr:anchor>1855</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="machine">unstable/813</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-813.xml</fr:route><fr:title text="" /><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>The inverse to the <fr:link href="jms-00KI.xml" title="Closure of functions under identity and composition" addr="jms-00KI" type="local">identity function</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {id}_{A}\colon  A\to  A]]></fr:tex> is simply itself.</fr:p>
 <fr:p>Fix <fr:link href="jms-00KR.xml" title="Bijection" addr="jms-00KR" type="local">bijections</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\to  B]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g\colon  B\to  C]]></fr:tex>, so that we have <fr:link href="jms-00KR.xml" title="Bijection" addr="jms-00KR" type="local">inverses</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f^{-1}\colon  B\to  A]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g^{-1}\colon  C\to  B]]></fr:tex>. The <fr:link href="jms-00KR.xml" title="Bijection" addr="jms-00KR" type="local">inverse</fr:link> to the <fr:link href="jms-00KI.xml" title="Closure of functions under identity and composition" addr="jms-00KI" type="local">composite function</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g\circ  f\colon  A \to  C]]></fr:tex> is the <fr:link href="jms-00KI.xml" title="Closure of functions under identity and composition" addr="jms-00KI" type="local">composite</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f^{-1}\circ  g^{-1}\colon  C \to  A]]></fr:tex>. The <fr:link href="jms-00KS.xml" title="Section-retraction pair" addr="jms-00KS" type="local">section/retraction</fr:link> conditions follow by those for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g]]></fr:tex> using the <fr:link href="jms-00IP.xml" title="Associativity and unit laws of relational composition" addr="jms-00IP" type="local">associative and unit laws of composition</fr:link>.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
